hopobject.body: Do you know what extension he's on? paxil zoloft prozac “Oh, drat!” cried my mother. She fumbled in her bag for her umbrella – which was scarcely big enough for one person, let alone two. Across the street, artists ran to cover their paintings with plastic. The coffee vendor was pulling down the shutters on his cart. We hurried across and just as we made it to the other side, a fat drop of rain splashed on my cheek. Sporadic brown circles – widely spaced, big as dimes – began to pop up on the pavement.
